00:05:53.970 --> 00:05:58.470
a role in determining
the timbre of the sound

00:05:58.470 --> 00:05:59.610
that you're hearing.

00:05:59.610 --> 00:06:00.300
OK.

00:06:00.300 --> 00:06:03.720
So that's kind of
the motivation.

00:06:03.720 --> 00:06:06.930
Another motivation is that
thinking about signals

00:06:06.930 --> 00:06:08.580
in terms of their
harmonic structure

00:06:08.580 --> 00:06:12.820
can provide important
insights into the signals.

00:06:12.820 --> 00:06:16.230
And so for example in music,
the harmonic structure

00:06:16.230 --> 00:06:20.690
is what determines
consonance and dissonance.

00:06:20.690 --> 00:06:21.570
Dissonance.

00:06:21.570 --> 00:06:29.090
So I'm going to play
two different notes that

00:06:29.090 --> 00:06:32.930
are related by an octave
shift, by a fifth shift,

00:06:32.930 --> 00:06:38.140
and adjacent notes in
the semitone scale.

00:06:38.140 --> 00:06:42.610
And below it, I've illustrated
